TI: [Proliferative activity of the matrix cells in lateral ventricles and granule cells in the dentate gyrus of the hippocampus in rats after pre- and postnatal alcoholic intoxication].
AB: The treatment of pregnant and lactating female rats with ethanol inhibits the proliferation of matrix cells in the lateral brain ventricles of fetuses and, during the early postnatal period, of granule cells in the dentate gyrus and cells of the ventral horn of Ammon. A low proliferation rate leads to a decrease in the number of neurons forming the granule layer of the dentate gyrus and pyramidal neurons in the CA-1 field of the horn of Ammon.
AD: Beritashvili Institute of Physiology, Academy of Sciences of Georgia, ul. Gotua 14, Tbilisi, 380060 Georgia.
TT: Proliferativnaia aktivnost' matrichnykh kletok bokovykh zheludochkov i granuliarnykh kletok zubchatoi izviliny gippokampa krys v usloviiakh pre- i postnatal'noi alkogol'noi intoksikatsii.
SO: Izv Akad Nauk Ser Biol. 2001 Jan-Feb;(1):117-20.
